cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about a new architecture for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the reduction of network parameters and memory footprint, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed architecture is based on progressive filtering, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions that their method does not rely on a postprocessing stage with Conditional Random Fields, which is a common technique in neural networks, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents results on two popular datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of multimedia, cs.MM (Multimedia).
